					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>It seems to be increasingly difficult to find a phone which is no more than a phone...however, next time you travel to the 'developing world' you will find a whole range of models (at about the $10 mark) which can only make and receive calls and send and receive texts. There are also rarely locked so they can be used in the UK.</p><p>And they have screens which display text large enough to be read without glasses, nothing in colour, no silly graphics, no internet access, no cameras, no bloody 'autotext' (my pet peeve), no music players, no video, nothing to make the tea, no GPS....in fact nothing except a telephone which works.....luxury!</p>
						
					</div>
